==English==

===Etymology===
Latin for ''for the rest, I am of the opinion...'' or ''in other respects, I advise...''.  From [[w:Cato the Elder|Cato the Elder]], who ended all of his speeches, no matter what subject he had discussed, with 'ceterum censeo Carthaginem esse delendam' : ''for the rest, I am of the opinion that Carthage is to be destroyed''.

===Idiom===
'''ceterum censeo'''
# a formulaic expression used to end a speech by reinforcing one, often unrelated, major view.

